PURPOSE AND SUMMARY
H.R. 3657, the ‘‘Hydropower Licensing Transparency Act’’, was
introduced by Representative Schrier (D–WA) on May 29, 2025.
The legislation would require the Federal Energy Regulatory Com-
mission to report periodically to Congress on the status of licensing
and relicensing applications for hydropower dams.
BACKGROUND AND NEED FOR LEGISLATION
Hydropower is one of the world’s oldest energy sources and con-
tinues to play an important role for our nation’s energy supply, pro-
viding power to approximately 30 million homes and businesses
across the United States.1 Additionally, hydropower accounts for 40
percent of the nation’s black start capacity for grid recovery fol-
lowing a major disruption.2
