SECTION-BY-SECTION ANALYSIS OF THE LEGISLATION
Section 1. Short title
This section provides the short title of ‘‘Hydropower Relicensing
Transparency Act.’’
Section 2. Annual licensing status report
This section amends the Federal Power Act by requiring an an-
nual report from the Commission to Congress on the status of cer-
tain hydropower licenses under sections 15(b)(1) and 4(e) of the
Federal Power Act. The report shall include: the date a notice of
intent was provided to the Commission; any assigned docket num-
ber; whether an application has been filed; information regarding
the status of such application; any upcoming proceeding related to
the new license; any ongoing or completed actions required of the
Commissions, other agencies, or the licensee. The information in
the report is required to be disaggregated based on license type.
